T*
() Tj
T*
(17. Deferred Work) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(What Is Deferred Work?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(When a customer declines or defers an estimate line, the system creates a Deferred Work) Tj
T*
(record. This is work that was recommended but not approved.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(For management, this is captured revenue. Deferred work represents jobs the customer) Tj
T*
(didn't approve today ? but might approve next visit, next month, or when reminded.) Tj
T*
(Without tracking it, this revenue simply disappears.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(What You Can Do with Deferred Work) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(| Action | What Happens |) Tj
T*
(|---|---|) Tj
T*
(| Remind | Send the customer a reminder about the deferred item |) Tj
T*
(| Book into New Job | Create a new job from the deferred work |) Tj
T*
(| Close / Expire | Mark the deferred work as no longer relevant |) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why It Matters for Revenue) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Deferred work is revenue you haven't captured yet. The system keeps it visible so the) Tj
T*
(team can follow up when the timing is right ? next service visit, seasonal promotion,) Tj
T*
(etc. Management can track the total deferred value and measure follow-up conversion over) Tj
T*
(time.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(18. Notifications) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(How Notifications Work) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. An event occurs \(inspection submitted, approval received, etc.\)) Tj
T*
(2. A notification record is created in the database) Tj
T*
(3. If a webhook is configured, the notification is queued for delivery) Tj
T*
(4. Delivery is retried with exponential backoff on failure) Tj
T*
(5. If no webhook exists, the notification is marked as "sent" \(no-op\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
ET
endstream
endobj
